souls (tie with repentance with 10–13)","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.10?lang=eng","category":"Worth & Value","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Corinthians 3:16-17","text":"Body is a temple","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-cor/3.16-17?lang=eng","category":"Worth & Value","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Quran 5:32","text":"\"If anyone saved a life, it would be as if he saved the life of all humankind\"","link":"","category":"Worth & Value","subcategory":""},{"author":"C. S. Lewis","reference":"The Weight of Glory, p.14-15","text":"\"It is a serious thing to live in a society of possible gods and goddesses, to remember that the dullest most uninteresting person you can talk to may one day be a creature which, if you saw it now, you would be strongly tempted to worship. [...] There are no ordinary people. You have never talked to a mere mortal. Nations, cultures, arts, civilization — these are mortal, and their life is to ours as the life of a gnat. But it is immortals whom we joke with, work with, marry, snub, and exploit\"","link":"","category":"Worth & Value","subcategory":"0misc"},{"author":"","reference":"Mosiah 4:16-26","text":"Withhold not from giving, for all is given to us","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.16-26?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Giving"},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 25:35-40","text":"I was hungered, and ye gave me meat…","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/25.35-40?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Giving"},{"author":"","reference":"James 2:15-17","text":"Practical religion. If the hungry ask for food, and you say \"go forth filled\", but give nothing, what does it accomplish?","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/james/2.15-17?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Giving"},{"author":"","reference":"1 Corinthians 10:24","text":"\"Let no man seek his own, but every man another's wealth\"","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-cor/10.24?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Giving"},{"author":"","reference":"2 Corinthians 9:7","text":"God loveth a cheerful giver","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/2-cor/9.7?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Giving"},{"author":"","reference":"Mosiah 18:29","text":"Minister to both spiritual and physical needs","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.29?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Giving"},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 12:9","text":"Love genuinely; cleave to good","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/12.9?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Caring"},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 12:15","text":"Rejoice/weep with those who rejoice/weep","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/12.15?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Caring"},{"author":"","reference":"Luke 10:30-37","text":"Good Samaritan","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/luke/10.30-37?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Caring"},{"author":"","reference":"Moroni 7:45-47","text":"Charity","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.45-47?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Caring"},{"author":"Horace Mann","reference":"","text":"“To pity distress is but human; to relieve it is godlike.”","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Caring"},{"author":"President Monson","reference":"Oct. 2010, Relief Society","text":"“There is a serious need for the charity that gives attention to those who are unnoticed, hope to those who are discouraged, aid to those who are afflicted. True charity is love in action. The need for charity is everywhere. Needed is the charity which refuses to find satisfaction in hearing or in repeating the reports of misfortunes that come to others, unless by so doing, the unfortunate one may be benefited.”","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Caring"},{"author":"","reference":"Mosiah 2:17","text":"Service of neighbor, service of God","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/2.17?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Discipleship"},{"author":"","reference":"John 13:34-35","text":"Love one another as I have loved; this is how you can identify a disciple of Christ","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/13.34-35?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Discipleship"},{"author":"","reference":"John 13:4-15","text":"Jesus washes feet","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/13.4-15?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Discipleship"},{"author":"President Nelson","reference":"Apr. 2023, Sunday Morning","text":"\"One of the easiest ways to identify a true follower of Jesus Christ is how compassionately that person treats other people\"","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Discipleship"},{"author":"Elder Gong","reference":"Oct. 2023, Sunday Afternoon","text":"\"The more compassionate, faithful, and selfless our service and sacrifice are in Him, the more we may begin to fathom Jesus Christ's atoning compassion and grace for us\"","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"Discipleship"},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 5:23-24","text":"Well with others before religious offering","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/5.23-24?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 5:44-45","text":"Love enemies","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/5.44-45?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 5:48","text":"Love perfectly","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/5.48?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 12:14","text":"Bless those who persecute you","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/12.14?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 13:7-8","text":"Owe no man anything save for love","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/13.7-8?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 13:10","text":"Love fulfills the law","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/13.10?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Mark 12:29-31","text":"The two great commandments","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/mark/12.29-31?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 13:9-10","text":"All commandments are summarized by love thy neighbor","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/13.9-10?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"1 Corinthians 13:4-7","text":"Definition and attributes of charity","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-cor/13.4-7?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 12:9-21","text":"Beautiful advice to the saints: cleave to good, hope, patience, work hard, love enemies, weep with those that weep, be humble","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/12.9-21?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"Elder Sabin","reference":"Oct. 2023, Saturday Evening","text":"\"In God's eyes, kindness is synonymous with greatness\"","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"Sister Runia","reference":"Oct. 2023, Saturday Evening","text":"\"We have neither God's authority to condemn, nor his power to redeem, but we have been authorized to exercise His love\"","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"D&C 121:41","text":"Maintain influence only by persuasion, gentleness, and love—in the same breath as the passage in the beginning of the chapter (suffering)","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/121.41?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"C.S. Lewis","reference":"Mere Christianity","text":"“When you have reached your own room, be kind to those who have chosen different doors and to those who are still in the hall. If they are wrong they need your prayers all the more; and if they are your enemies, then you are under orders to pray for them. This is one of the rules common to the whole house.”","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Colossians 3:12-15","text":"Be charitable and let the peace of God dwell in your hearts","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/col/3.12-15?lang=eng","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"Elder Haight","reference":"","text":"“The Lord isn’t going to be concerned about whether you were a bishop, or [a] stake president, or [an] apostle. He’s going to be concerned about how you treated people.”","link":"","category":"Love one another","subcategory":"The Commandment"},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 6:14-18","text":"Forgive trespasses","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/6.14-18?lang=eng","category":"Forgiveness","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 18:21-22","text":"How oft shall I forgive my brother?","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/18.21-22?lang=eng","category":"Forgiveness","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 18:23-35","text":"King forgives servant, servant doesn't forgive; king angry","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/18.23-35?lang=eng","category":"Forgiveness","subcategory":""},{"author":"Mencius","reference":"","text":"\"Though you denude yourself and insult me, what is that to me? You cannot defile my soul by your outrage\"","link":"","category":"Forgiveness","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Ephesians 4:26","text":"Let not the sun go down upon your wrath","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/eph/4.26?lang=eng","category":"Forgiveness","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 7:2","text":"Don't judge","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/7.2?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Jacob 2:35","text":"The sobbings of their hearts will rise up against you; there is justice for the wounded","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/jacob/2.35?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 36:13-15","text":"Remembrance of sins, shame to stand before God","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.13-15?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 41:6-8","text":"We judge ourselves with our choices","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/41.6-8?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 41:15","text":"Karma, kinda","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/41.15?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Holland","reference":"Borne upon Eagles’ Wings","text":"“It's one thing to reap in kind, but we reap, somehow, always in greater quantity. We sow a little thistle, and we get a lot of thistle—years and years of it, big bushes and branches of it.”","link":"","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mormon 9:3-4","text":"More miserable with guilt close to God than far away","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/morm/9.3-4?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mormon 8:20","text":"\"Vengeance and judgment are mine\"","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/morm/8.20?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 12:18-19","text":"Live in peace, \"vengeance is mine\"","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/12.18-19?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 18:6","text":"Hurt kids, better if you drowned","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/18.6?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 3:19-21","text":"Those who do evil don't want light; own condemnation","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/3.19-21?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"Saigo","reference":"Bushido (Nitobe), p.82","text":"\"The Way is the way of Heaven and Earth; Man's place is to follow it; therefore make it the object of thy life to reverence Heaven. Heaven loves me and others with equal love; therefore with the love wherewith thou lovest thyself, love others. Make not Man thy partner, but Heaven, and making Heaven thy partner do the best. Never condemn others; but see to it that thou comes not short of thine own mark\"","link":"","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Peter 3:16-17","text":"Better to be tried for good deeds than bad","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-pet/3.16-17?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 33:11","text":"You and I shall stand face to face before His bar, and ye shall know that I have been commanded to write these things","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/33.11?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 12:14-15","text":"Our shame and guilt would cause us to wish mountains and rocks would come and cover us before the presence of God; we will acknowledge the justice and mercy in His judgements","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/12.14-15?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Helaman 13:38","text":"“Ye have sought for happiness in doing iniquity,” “sought [...] that which ye could not obtain”","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/hel/13.38?lang=eng","category":"Justice & Judgement","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Isaiah 54","text":"Pretty description of Zion/gathering of Israel","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/isa/54?lang=eng","category":"Latter days","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mark 13:31-37","text":"Watch for Second Coming","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/mark/13.31-37?lang=eng","category":"Latter days","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Isaiah 52:9","text":"Break forth into joy, ye waste places of Jerusalem","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/isa/52.9?lang=eng","category":"Latter days","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Moses 7:18","text":"The Lord called His people Zion","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.18?lang=eng","category":"Latter days","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 6:22-24","text":"Single-minded, single eye","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/6.22-24?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 6:19-21","text":"Lay not treasures on Earth, but in Heaven","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/6.19-21?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 6:38","text":"Came not to do my will, but Him who sent me","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/6.38?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Acts 17:23","text":"\"To the unknown God\"","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/acts/17.23?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 21:15-17","text":"Do you love me? Feed my sheep… Do you love me more than fishy? Stop fishing and go preach","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/21.15-17?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Corinthians 3:18-19","text":"Be not wise in the ways of the world","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-cor/3.18-19?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Proverbs 4:26","text":"Ponder the path of thy feet","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/prov/4.26?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Corinthians 4:18","text":"Things which are seen, temporal; things which are not seen, eternal","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/2-cor/4.18?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 28:24-25","text":"Wo be unto him that is at ease in Zion; keep in mind always your objective lest you slip into complacency","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/28.24-25?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Jacob 2:19","text":"Obtaining riches is good if done with the intent to use them for the good of others","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/jacob/2.19?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Maxwell","reference":"Apr. 1974, Sunday Afternoon","text":"\"If you have not chosen the kingdom of God first, it will in the end make no difference what you have chosen instead\"","link":"","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Waddell","reference":"Oct. 2023, Sunday Morning","text":"The problem for the Israelite was not the gold they brought, but what they allowed it to become: an idol","link":"","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Holland","reference":"The Will of the Father","text":"“The path to a complete Christian education passes through the Garden of Gethsemane, and we will learn there if we haven't learned it before that our Father will have no other gods before him—even (or especially) if that would-be god is our self.”","link":"","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Holland","reference":"The Will of the Father","text":"“We must be willing to place all that we have—not just our possessions (they may be the easiest things of all to give up), but also our ambition and pride and stubbornness and vanity—we must place it all on the altar of God, kneel there in silent submission, and willingly walk away.”","link":"","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"George MacDonald","reference":"","text":"“There is one kind of religion in which the more devoted a man is, the fewer proselytes he makes: the worship of himself.”","link":"","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"3 Nephi 11:40","text":"If you establish more or less for doctrine, you build upon a sandy foundation","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/11.40?lang=eng","category":"Distractions & Idols","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 8:31-36","text":"The truth shall make you free","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/8.31-36?lang=eng","category":"Liberty & Freedom","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 6:18","text":"Free from sin, servants of right","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/6.18?lang=eng","category":"Liberty & Freedom","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 30:7-9","text":"Freedom of religion","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.7-9?lang=eng","category":"Liberty & Freedom","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 8:34","text":"Servant of sin","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/8.34?lang=eng","category":"Liberty & Freedom","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"D&C 82:10","text":"Covenants","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/82.10?lang=eng","category":"Promises & Covenants","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 14:26","text":"HG is comforter, brings into remembrance","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/14.26?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Helaman 5:30","text":" pierces soul, but is perfectly still","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/hel/5.30?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 32:5","text":"If ye enter by the way and receive the Holy Ghost, it shall show you all things that ye should do","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/32.5?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Ether 4:11","text":"Spirit will visit believer","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/ether/4.11?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Ether 4:12","text":"\"Whatsoever persuadeth men to do good is of me\"","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/ether/4.12?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Moses 6:61","text":"Role of the Spirit","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.61?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Galatians 5:22","text":"Fruit of Spirit is love, joy, peace, ...","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/gal/5.22?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 14:18","text":"I will not leave you comfortless","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/14.18?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Kings 19:11-12","text":"Still small voice","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/19.11-12?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Nephi 4:6","text":"Led by the Spirit without knowing what to do beforehand","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/4.6?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Corinthians 12:7-12","text":"Gifts of the Spirit are several, members of the church are as members of the same body","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-cor/12.7-12?lang=eng","category":"Holy Ghost","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Timothy 1:7","text":"God gave spirit of power, love, and sound mind; not fear","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt