.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rev/7.14?lang=eng","category":"Overcoming Trials","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 32:14-16","text":"Blessed are those who humble themselves without being compelled, by choice","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/32.14-16?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 7:23-24","text":"Be good people, humble, patient","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/7.23-24?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 26:11-12","text":"I will boast not of my strength, which I have not, but that of my God","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/26.11-12?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 12:16","text":"Be not wise in your own conceits","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/12.16?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 18:1-4","text":"Children, greatest in the kingdom of Heaven","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/18.1-4?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 19:23-24","text":"Rich man, camel (read 25, 26; only possible through grace of God)","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/19.23-24?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 19:30","text":"First shall be the last, and the last shall be first","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/19.30?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 20:26-28","text":"Great in the Church? Serve the least; even as Christ, greatest of all, died for all","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/20.26-28?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 23:12","text":"Whosoever shall exalt himself shall be abased","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/23.12?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"James 3:13-14","text":"Don't be arrogant","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/james/3.13-14?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Corinthians 4:7","text":"If you all received, why do you glory in what you have?","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-cor/4.7?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 5:28","text":"Behold, are ye stripped of pride? If ye are not, ye are not prepared to meet God","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.28?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Proverbs 29:23","text":"A man's pride shall bring him low, honor shall uphold the humble","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/prov/29.23?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"C. S. Lewis","reference":"","text":"“Pride gets no pleasure out of having something, only out of having more of it than the next man. [...] It is the comparison that makes you proud: the pleasure of being above the rest. Once the element of competition has gone, pride has gone.”","link":"","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"C. S. Lewis","reference":"","text":"“Do not imagine that if you meet a really humble man he will be what most people call ‘humble’ nowadays: he will not be a [...] person [...] who is always telling you that, of course, he is nobody. Probably all you will think about him is that he seemed a cheerful, intelligent chap who took a real interest in what you said to him. [...] He will not be thinking about humility: he will not be thinking about himself at all.”","link":"","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Maxwell","reference":"Patience","text":"“The patient person assumes that what others have to say is worth listening to. A patience person is not so chronically eager to put forth his or her own ideas. In true humility, we do some waiting upon others. We value them for what they say and what they have to contribute. Patience and humility are special friends.”","link":"","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 38:10-12","text":"Do not boast or lift yourself in pride, be bold but not overbearing, bridle the passions that you may be filled with love: be temperate","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/38.10-12?lang=eng","category":"Humility","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mosiah 27:29","text":"My soul hath been redeemed","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.29?lang=eng","category":"Healing & Redeeming","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"3 Nephi 17:7","text":"Bring the sick and afflicted, I will have mercy","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/17.7?lang=eng","category":"Healing & Redeeming","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 8:5-13","text":"Centurion story; healing, faith among gentiles","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/8.5-13?lang=eng","category":"Healing & Redeeming","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mark 5:24-34","text":"Heals woman with blood issue, see note on women in Christianity","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/mark/5.24-34?lang=eng","category":"Healing & Redeeming","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mark 5:22-43","text":"Christ heals girl privately, immediately says to keep secret and feed her","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/mark/5.22-43?lang=eng","category":"Healing & Redeeming","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Luke 7:36-47","text":"Sinn