nd priests must work with their own hands to support themselves","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.24-26?lang=eng","category":"Tithing & Fasting","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mosiah 18:27","text":"Redistribution according to means","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.27?lang=eng","category":"Tithing & Fasting","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"D&C 121:7-8","text":"Peace be unto thee, my son","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/121.7-8?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 5:9","text":"Blessed are the peacemakers","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/5.9?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 10:34-37","text":"Jesus Christ sends not peace, but sword; sets household at variance","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/10.34-37?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Isaiah 52:7","text":"How beautiful upon the mountain are the feet of Him that publisheth peace","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/isa/52.7?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"James 3:18","text":"Righteousness: peace","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/james/3.18?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Nephi 13:37","text":"Blessed are they who build Zion, beautiful upon the mountain who publish peace","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/13.37?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 14:27","text":"Peace I leave unto you… Not as the world giveth","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/14.27?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Moroni 7:3","text":"Peaceable followers of Christ will enter into His rest: for now and forever","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.3?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mosiah 15:14-18","text":"How beautiful upon the mountain… ","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/15.14-18?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Philippians 4:6-7","text":"Don't worry, pray with gratitude, and the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will fill you","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/philip/4.6-7?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"3 Nephi 11:30","text":"This is not my doctrine, to stir up the hearts of men against each other","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/11.30?lang=eng","category":"Peace","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 31:18-20","text":"Endure to the end","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.18-20?lang=eng","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Jacob 3:2","text":"Those that are pure of heart may receive His pleasing word and feast on His love forever if they remain firm","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/jacob/3.2?lang=eng","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Omni 1:26","text":"Offer your whole souls unto Him, then endure to the end: recipe for salvation","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/omni/1.26?lang=eng","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Mosiah 2:41","text":"Those who keep commandments to the end will live with God in a state of never-ending happiness","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/2.41?lang=eng","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Maxwell","reference":"Patience","text":"“Patience is, therefore, clearly not fatalistic, shoulder-shrugging resignation. It is the acceptance of a divine rhythm to life; it is obedience prolonged.”","link":"","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Maxwell","reference":"Patience","text":"“Patience is never condescending or exclusive—it is never glad when others are left out. Patience never preens itself; it prefers keeping the window of the soul open.”","link":"","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Maxwell","reference":"Patience","text":"“Very importantly, it is patience, when combined with love, which permits us ‘in process of time’ to detoxify our disappointments. Patience and love take the radioactivity out of our resentments.”","link":"","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Maxwell","reference":"Patience","text":"“Patience helps us to use, rather than to protest, these seeming flat periods of life, becoming filled with quiet wonder over the past and with anticipation for that which may lie ahead, instead of demeaning the particular flatness through which we may be passing at the time.”","link":"","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Job 1:21","text":"The Lord gave, and the Lord hath taken away; blessed be the name of the Lord","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/job/1.21?lang=eng","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Thessalonians 5:14","text":"Support the weak, be patient with everybody","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-thes/5.14?lang=eng","category":"Perseverance & Patience","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 28:12","text":"Loss of loved ones","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/28.12?lang=eng","category":"Grief & Loss","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Job 3:1-26","text":"Job wishes he had never been born","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/job/3.1-26?lang=eng","category":"Grief & Loss","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Psalms 10:1","text":"“Hide not thy face far from me”\n\nSee also 22:1-2, 27:9, 28:1","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/ps/10.1?lang=eng","category":"Grief & Loss","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"D&C 121:1-3","text":"“How long shall thy hand be stayed…? Yeah, O Lord, how long…?”","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/121.1-3?lang=eng","category":"Grief & Loss","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 28:13-14","text":"Sorrow for death, joy for life; discord of dark, reason of light","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/28.13-14?lang=eng","category":"Bitter & Sweet","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 12:21","text":"Overcome evil with good","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/12.21?lang=eng","category":"Bitter & Sweet","subcategory":""},{"author":"Mencius","reference":"","text":"\"Benevolence brings under its sway whatever hinders its power, just as water subdues fire. They only doubt the power of water to quench flames who try to extinguish with a cupful a whole burning wagon-load of sticks and branches\"","link":"","category":"Bitter & Sweet","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"D&C 29:39-40","text":"If they should never have bitter, no sweet","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/29.39-40?lang=eng","category":"Bitter & Sweet","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 6:23","text":"Sin, death; righteousness, life","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/6.23?lang=eng","category":"Bitter & Sweet","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 8:6","text":"Carnal: death; spiritual: life/peace","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/8.6?lang=eng","category":"Bitter & Sweet","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 2:11-13","text":"No opposition: ultimately, no God","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/2.11-13?lang=eng","category":"Bitter & Sweet","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Helaman 12:15","text":"Heliocentrism","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/hel/12.15?lang=eng","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 16:2-3","text":"Red sky at morning, sailor take warning; red sky at night, sailor's delight","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/16.2-3?lang=eng","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Moses 1:27-32","text":"Many lands, worlds, inhabitants; numberless as grains on shore","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.27-32?lang=eng","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Moses 1:37","text":"They are numbered to me, for they are mine","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.37?lang=eng","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Moses 1:38","text":"As one earth shall pass, another shall come","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.38?lang=eng","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Boethius","reference":"","text":"\"Even chance, which seems to hurtle on, unreigned,/ Submits to the bridle and government of law\"","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Kaplan","reference":"Chances Are, p.13","text":"\"Once you know that daisies usually have an odd number of petals, you can get anyone to love you\"","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Kaplan","reference":"Chances Are, p.22","text":"\"Since God is perfect and infinite, we cannot comprehend Him — but our God-given reason is ample for understanding His creation. All speculation about the physical world becomes permissible because, in the opposed rhythm of speculation and doubt, we progressively refine our concepts toward the vivid, the clear, and the distinct. The more crystalline our ideas, the more closely we approach Divine Truth — although we can no more reach it than we can plot every point in a line.\"","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Kaplan","reference":"Chances Are, p.21","text":"Astronomy endowed us with the notion of physical law","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Kaplan","reference":"Chances Are, p.19","text":"Power law, horse racing analogy","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Kaplan","reference":"Chances Are, p.10","text":"Llull's machine to convert the Moors","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Kaplan","reference":"Chances Are, p.26","text":"\"For Pascal, the mystical prevalence of pattern was evidence of design and spiritual meaning; for scientists, it is an invitation to explore the unknown, promising that the seemingly random has hidden structure\"","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"St. Augustine","reference":"","text":"\"What is time? Ask me not, and I know. Ask me, and I cannot tell you\"","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Rabbi Lord Jonathan Sacks","reference":"","text":"“What the secularists forgot is that Homo Sapiens is the meaning-seeking animal. If there is one thing that great institutions of the modern world do not do, it is provide meaning.”","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Einstein","reference":"Where Is Science Going?","text":"“Personally I am inclined to agree with Schopenhauer in thinking that one of the strongest motives that lead people to give their lives to art and science is the urge to flee from everyday life, with its drab deadly dullness, and thus unshackle the chains of one’s own transient desires, which supplant one another in an interminable succession so long as the mind is fixed on the horizon of daily environment.”","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Einstein","reference":"Where Is Science Going?","text":"“Human nature always has tried to form for itself a simple and synoptic image of the surrounding world. In doing this it tries to construct a picture which will give some sort of tangible expression to what the human mind sees in nature. That is what the poet does, and the painter, and the speculative philosopher and the natural philosopher, each in his own way. Within this picture he places the centre of gravity of his own soul, so that he will find in it the rest and equilibrium which he cannot find within the narrow circle of his restless personal reactions to everyday life.”","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Einstein","reference":"Where Is Science Going?","text":"“Thus the supreme task of the physicist is the discovery of the most general elementary laws from which the world-picture can be deduced logically. But there is no logical way to the discovery of these elementary laws. There is only the way of intuition, which is helped by a feeling for the order lying behind experience.”","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Einstein","reference":"Where Is Science Going?","text":"“I have often heard that [Planck's] colleagues are in the habit of tracing this attitude to his extraordinary personal gifts of energy and discipline. I believe they are wrong. The state of mind which furnishes the driving power here resembles that of the devotee or the lover. The long-sustained effort is not inspired by any set plan or purpose. Its inspiration arises from a hunger of the soul.”","link":"","category":"Science & Mathematics","subcategory":""},{"author":"Nitobe","reference":"Bushido, p.55","text":"Kenshin gave Shingen salt after Hojo Prince cut him off; \"I do not fight with salt, but with the sword\"","link":"","category":"Honor & Grace","subcategory":""},{"author":"Nietzsche","reference":"","text":"\"You are to be proud of your enemy; then the success of your enemy is your success also\"","link":"","category":"Honor & Grace","subcategory":""},{"author":"Spencer","reference":"","text":"\"Grace is the most economical manner of motion\"; \"Fine manners, therefore, mean power in repose\"","link":"","category":"Honor & Grace","subcategory":""},{"author":"Nitobe","reference":"Bushido, p.120","text":"\"To be beaten is to conquer\"","link":"","category":"Honor & Grace","subcategory":""},{"author":"Wan Yang Ming","reference":"","text":"\"To know and to act are one and the same\"","link":"","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"D&C 11:21","text":"Seek first to obtain word","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/11.21?lang=eng","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"Confucius","reference":"","text":"\"Learning without thought is labor lost; thought without learning is a peril\"","link":"","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 28:30","text":"Line upon line, precept upon precept","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/28.30?lang=eng","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 31:14","text":"Burden of knowledge; If ye receive a testimony, are baptized, receive the Holy Ghost, but then deny me — it would have been better if ye had never even known me","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.14?lang=eng","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Jacob 4:8","text":"How unsearchable are the depths of the mysteries of Him; all the knowledge we have is revealed","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/jacob/4.8?lang=eng","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"D&C 93:29","text":"Truth cannot be created or made; man was in the beginning with God","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.29?lang=eng","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Maxwell","reference":"Patience","text":"“Deep within us, His doctrines do strike the promised chord of familiarity and underscore our true identity. Our sense of belonging grows in spite of our sense of separateness; for His teachings stir our souls, awakening feelings within us which have somehow survived underneath the encrusting experiences of mortality.”","link":"","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Holland","reference":"Borne upon Eagles’ Wings","text":"“This is the most auspicious occasion of our year. It is better than Christmas. It's better than Thanksgiving. It's even better than Mother's Day. It's better because we're enlightened, and that's as close as we come to being free.”","link":"","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"Plato","reference":"","text":"“It is better to be unborn than untaught, for ignorance is at the root of all misfortune.”","link":"","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"Sam Johnson","reference":"","text":"“Ignorance, when voluntary, is criminal, and a man may be properly charged with that evil which he neglected or refused to learn how to prevent.”","link":"","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"The Gift of Self, p.151-53","text":"Glazed brick story (“Borne upon Eagles’ Wings”, Holland)","link":"","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"1 Timothy 4:15","text":"“Meditate upon these things; give thyself wholly to them”","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/1-tim/4.15?lang=eng","category":"Knowledge","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Ecclesiastes 9:3-12","text":"Live well and happily, since nothing you have or do can compete with time","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/ot/eccl/9.3-12?lang=eng","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 6:34","text":"The morrow will take care of its own evils","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/6.34?lang=eng","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Romans 8:28","text":"All things work together for good to those who love God","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/rom/8.28?lang=eng","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"Prince of Shirakawa","reference":"Bushido, p.63","text":"\"Though they come stealing in the silent watches of the night, drive not away, but rather cherish these — the fragrance of flowers, the sound of distant bells, the insect hummings of a frosty night\"","link":"","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"Elder Sabin","reference":"Oct. 2023, Saturday Evening","text":"\"We are surrounded by innumerable blessings that we can easily take for granted if we are not mindful. Conversely, when nothing is expected and everything is appreciated, life becomes magical.\"","link":"","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"President Nelson","reference":"Oct. 2023, Sunday Afternoon","text":"\"The very things that will make your mortal life the best it can be are exactly the same things that will make your life throughout all eternity the best it can be.\"","link":"","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"Emmerson","reference":"","text":"“If the stars should appear one night in a thousand years, how would men believe and adore; and preserve for many generations the remembrance of the city of God which had been shown them.”","link":"","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Philippians 4:8","text":"If there is anything good, virtuous, lovely… think on these things","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/philip/4.8?lang=eng","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Philippians 4:11","text":"I have learned to be content in any state","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/philip/4.11?lang=eng","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Colossians 3:23","text":"Whatever you do, do it heartily unto the Lord","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/col/3.23?lang=eng","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"C. S. Lewis","reference":"The Screwtape Letters","text":"“For the Present is the point at which time touches eternity”","link":"","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":""},{"author":"Robert Fulghum","reference":"We Learned It All in Kindergarten","text":"A great little text about how all important wisdom is taught through simple things","link":"https://docs.google.com/document/u/0/d/1N1d9i1FPeAzQdExhc7iDm7TqPFDgfeCoOj1xh_LDX3w/edit","category":"Gratitude & Good Living","subcategory":"0misc"},{"author":"","reference":"Alma 19:5","text":"\"To me, he doth not stink\" (King Lamoni)","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/19.5?lang=eng","category":"Funny","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Helaman 9:21","text":"\"Uncircumcised of heart\"","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.21?lang=eng","category":"Funny","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Ether 11:14","text":"Indireta","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/ether/11.14?lang=eng","category":"Funny","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"Matthew 21:18-19","text":"Jesus randomly curses a poor fig tree","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/matt/21.18-19?lang=eng","category":"Funny","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"John 9:25-33","text":"Lots of great comebacks in this chapter","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/nt/john/9.25-33?lang=eng","category":"Funny","subcategory":""},{"author":"","reference":"2 Nephi 18","text":"\"Seek the Lord, not peeping wizards\"","link":"https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/18?lang=eng","category":"Funny","subcategory":""},{"author":"J. Golden Kimball","reference":"","text":"“If I owned the two, I would rather live in hell and try rent St. George.”","link":"","category":"Funny","subcategory":""}]